---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Raga Yaman — Complete Lesson | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Learn Raga Yaman completely — India's most popular evening raga. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Raga Yaman — Complete Lesson</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-intermediate capitalize">intermediate</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 40 min · Intermediate</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Raga Yaman — Complete Lesson</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Learn Raga Yaman completely — India's most popular evening raga.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Always Tivra Ma (T key / F#) — natural Ma never appears</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Aroha starts from Ni below Sa: N R G M' P D N S</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vadi is Ga (D key) — return to it frequently</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Pakad: N R G comma M' G R S</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Evening raga — romantic yearning mood</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>Why Start with Yaman</h2>
      <p>Raga Yaman is the most recommended first raga for North Indian harmonium students. Its clear identity pleasant sound singable phrases and evening timing make it perfect for beginners. Most importantly it uses all natural swaras plus just one alteration (Tivra Ma) — making it theoretically simple while musically beautiful.</p>

      <h2>Complete Raga Profile</h2>
      <p>Thaat: Kalyan. Jati: Sampurna (all 7 swaras). Vadi: Ga. Samvadi: Ni. Time: First prahar of night (6 to 9 PM). Season: All year. Rasa: Shringara (romantic longing). The single defining rule: Tivra Ma (F sharp — T key) is always used. Natural Ma (F key) never appears in Yaman. Violating this rule instantly destroys the raga.</p>

      <h2>Aroha and Avaroha</h2>
      <p>Aroha: N R G M' P D N upper-S. Keys: J S D T G H J K. Note the aroha begins from Ni below Sa — a characteristic of Yaman. Avaroha: upper-S N D P M' G R S. Keys: K J H G T D S A. Practice each direction separately 20 times before combining ascending and descending into a continuous exercise.</p>

      <h2>The Pakad</h2>
      <p>N R G comma M' G R S. Keys: J S D pause T D S A. The comma represents a slight breath pause — do not rush through it. This phrase is Yaman's musical fingerprint. Master it until your fingers play it automatically without conscious thought. The pakad should be the first thing you play when sitting down to practice Yaman.</p>

      <h2>Simple Bandish in Yaman</h2>
      <p>Sthayi: N R G M' P bar D N upper-S N D P. Antara: upper-S R upper-G upper-S N D bar P M' G R S. Practice sthayi completely before adding antara. Once both sections are memorized practice connecting them smoothly. Record yourself playing this bandish and listen back — you will hear your own progress clearly.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>